[0.143, "o", "SESSION     IDENTITY   PID    COMMAND  STATUS  STARTED                 \r\n----------  ---------  -----  -------  ------  ------------------------\r\nalice-demo  alice      663    2.1.92   active  Mon Apr  6 20:30:00 2026\r\nbob-demo    bob        665    2.1.92   active  Mon Apr  6 20:30:00 2026\r\nns-tmesh    test-node  45667  zsh      active  Mon Apr  6 17:52:07 2026\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\n"]
[2.012, "o", "  --- Alice conversation log ---\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "[tmesh 2026-04-06 18:30:50] --> bob: Hi Bob, I am alice. I am refactoring the payment service. What are you working on?  (sent)\r\n"]
[1.515, "o", "[tmesh 2026-04-06 18:31:05] <-- bob [message]: Hey alice! I'm working on a database migration for the auth service. Adding a sessions table with token rotation support. Do you need any auth schema changes for the payment service refactor?\r\n"]
[1.518, "o", "[tmesh 2026-04-06 18:31:23] --> bob: Nice, that's adjacent work. Yes actually -- I'll need the new session token format for payment webhook auth. Can you share the sessions table schema when it's ready?  (sent)\r\n"]
[1.514, "o", "[tmesh 2026-04-06 18:31:29] <-- bob [message]: Sure thing. The new session tokens will be JWT with a service_scope claim. For payment webhooks you'll want scope='payment:webhook'. I'll expose a verify_token(token, scope) function in the auth SDK. Migration lands today -- I'll ping you when it's ready.\r\n"]
[1.514, "o", "[tmesh 2026-04-06 18:31:43] --> bob: Perfect, JWT with service_scope is exactly what I need. I'll wire up verify_token(token, 'payment:webhook') on my end once your SDK update lands. Thanks for the coordination, talk soon.  (sent)\r\n"]
[1.515, "o", "[tmesh 2026-04-06 18:31:48] <-- bob [message]: Sounds good. I'll make sure the migration includes a test fixture with a valid payment:webhook token so you can integration-test against it. Good luck with the refactor -- let's sync again once both PRs are up.\r\n"]
[1.515, "o", "[tmesh 2026-04-06 18:31:55] --> bob: Great call on the test fixture -- that'll save me time on integration tests. Cheers.  (sent)\r\n"]
[1.509, "o", "\r\n"]
